	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If you were raised in or drawn to Hinduism, the Father's Heart Bible™ is offered to you with deep respect.</strong> You carry a profound spiritual hunger — the longing to know the divine, to be free, to find rest from the long wheel of karma and striving. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> from beginning to end. Whether you searched "is there one God who loves me," "does God know my name," "Bible verses about God's love," or "who is God in the Bible" — it points to one gentle answer: the divine you seek is not distant or impersonal, but a personal Father who is near to every one of us, who calls you by name, and who offers His love as a gift of grace.`}
	keyTakeaway={`The divine you long for is one personal Father who knows your name, is near to you right now, and loves you as His own child — by grace, not by the weight of merit earned across lifetimes.`}
	painsHeading={`Longing for the divine`}
	painsIntroHtml={`Hinduism is vast and beautifully diverse — a heritage of devotion, philosophy, and sincere seeking shared by more than a billion people. Beneath that diversity runs a deep and honest longing: to truly know the divine, and to find rest. The numbers tell part of the story.`}
