	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Within Hinduism lives one of humanity's deepest streams of spiritual devotion — the discipline of bhakti, the love of the seeker for the divine, the patient pursuit of liberation through ritual, study, and merit. It honors a profound truth that many in the modern world have forgotten: that there is something sacred beyond us, worthy of our whole heart.</p><p>And within that devotion, many sincere hearts carry a quiet longing. The divine can feel vast yet distant; present in many forms, or, in the Vedanta tradition, an ultimate Absolute beyond name and personality. The path can feel like effort — the weight of karma carried across lifetimes, the striving to be free. So the heart wonders: is there One who knows <em>me</em> — my name, my story — and loves me, not for what I have earned, but simply as His own? This page is a gentle answer to that longing, offered with respect, not argument.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
