	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for Hindus`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here is what the Father's Heart Bible™ gently offers — not as a rival to your seeking, but as the heart it has always reached toward: the divine you long for is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong>. One personal, loving God who is near to every one of us, who knows you by name, and who calls you His own child.</p><p>So much spiritual life can feel like effort — the climb toward liberation, the weight of merit measured across lifetimes, the striving to draw close to a divine that can seem far off or impersonal. The Bible reveals something tender at the center of all things: a Father who comes near to you, who does not wait for you to earn His love, but offers it freely, as grace.</p><p>You do not have to ascend to Him by your own striving. He has come close to you. Before you are a seeker, a devotee, or a soul on the long wheel of becoming — you are known, and you are loved. Your Father says: I am not far from you. I know your name. You are Mine.</p>`}
