	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You do not have to decide everything today. Faith is not a leap demanded of you — it is an invitation to come and see. Read a little. Listen with an honest heart. The Father is patient, and He meets sincere seekers gently, one quiet step at a time.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I have watched you seek Me, and I have not been far from you for a moment. You have reached toward the divine across the years, and I want you to hear Me gently over all of it: I know your name. I know when you sit and when you rise. I am near to you now.</p><p>You do not have to climb to Me or earn My love across a thousand lifetimes. I am your Father, and I have already come near to you. You are My beloved child — not for what you have achieved, but because you are Mine. Come to Me, and rest."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for Hindus`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You for every sincere heart raised in the rich heritage of Hinduism — for their devotion, their longing for the divine, their hunger to be free. We honor the seeking You Yourself have placed within them.</p><p>Draw near to them, Father, as only You can. To every heart that has wondered whether the divine is distant, plural, or impersonal, reveal Yourself as one personal Father who is near, who knows them by name, and who loves them as His own child. Lift from them the weight of striving and merit, and let them taste the rest and the grace You freely give.</p><p>Let them encounter Your fatherly love — not as argument or pressure, but as the gentle, patient kindness of a Father welcoming a child home. Guard them, bless them, and meet them right where they are. May they know they are seen, known, and deeply loved by You.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
