	faqs={[
		{ question: `Is there one God who loves me?`, answer: `Yes. The Bible reveals one personal God who is near to every one of us (Acts 17:27) and who lavishes great love on us, calling us His own children (1 John 3:1). He is not distant or impersonal — He knows your name and loves you by grace. Read and hear these verses free, with audio, in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Does God know my name?`, answer: `Yes. Isaiah 43:1 says, "I have called you by name — you are Mine," and Psalm 139:1-3 says He has searched you and known you — your thoughts, your ways, your story. Among more than a billion souls, He knows you personally. You can read and listen to these passages free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about God's love?`, answer: `The Bible says God's love is a gift, not a wage. 1 John 3:1 marvels at the great love the Father has lavished on us; Romans 8:15 and Galatians 4:6 say He gives us His Spirit so we can call Him Abba, Father. His love is offered freely by grace, not earned by merit. Read these free, with audio, in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Who is God in the Bible — is He personal or impersonal?`, answer: `The Bible reveals God as deeply personal — a loving Father, not a distant or impersonal Absolute. He is near to each of us (Acts 17:27), knows us by name (Isaiah 43:1), and invites us to call Him Father (Romans 8:15). The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals Him as Father wherever Scripture does — read it free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio I can read for myself?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. Open fathersheartbible.com/read and read or hear any book for yourself, in your own time, with an open and honest heart.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different?`, answer: `It's a fresh English translation that reveals God as a Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father. For anyone who has longed for a divine that is near and personal rather than distant or impersonal, that reframes everything: you meet not a force to appease, but a Father who already knows your name and loves you as His own child.` },
		{ question: `How can I begin reading the Bible if I come from a Hindu background?`, answer: `Start gently and start free. Open fathersheartbible.com/read, and begin with a short, warm passage — Psalm 139, John 1, or Matthew 11 are gentle places to start. Listen to the audio as you read. There's no pressure and nothing to decide today; you're simply invited to come and see. Our how-to-pray guide and verses-by-topic pages can help you find words.` },
